item.title: NEAR DEATH AT SEAWORLD
item.description:
NEAR DEATH AT SEAWORLD
Near Death at SeaWorld. Serious aggression incident by the killer whale Kasatka against her trainer Ken Peters in 2006. More information in David Kirby's book: Death at Seaworld. Or visit http://www.deathatseaworld.com In the video, obtained via FOIA, Kasatka grabs her trainer's foot and will not let go, dunking him under the water for extended periods of time. Peters, who remains eerily calm, finally manages to free himself, only to have Kasatka charge him over the barrier net. This video was presented at trial in the case of SeaWorld v US Secretary of Labor Hilda Solis. Judge Ken Welsch, who ruled largely against the company, called the video "chilling" - More details are provided in DEATH AT SEAWORLD (St Martin's Press, July 17, 2012) www.deathatseaworld.com
